                    This makes his disadvantage when 7 is the main equal to 3∣d, and half a farthing
                    in the pound.</p>
                <p>The calculations applied to the main of 7 can easily be made use of for any other
                    main, when it will be found that the caster’s expectation of loss when 5 or 9 is
                    the main is 3⅛d. and half a farthing in the pound, and when 6 or 8 is the main
